1
00:00:13,540 --> 00:00:15,780
♪Trap my frame♪

2
00:00:15,980 --> 00:00:20,060
♪Plagues demand I bow in shame♪

3
00:00:20,780 --> 00:00:22,940
♪Snare my soul♪

4
00:00:23,020 --> 00:00:27,100
♪Rules command I swallow my pride♪

5
00:00:27,260 --> 00:00:30,620
♪Mock my way♪

6
00:00:30,900 --> 00:00:34,060
♪Chained me where I must stay♪

7
00:00:34,420 --> 00:00:36,780
♪Taught me to kneel, not to speak♪

8
00:00:37,020 --> 00:00:41,220
♪And to let my life pass by in silence♪

9
00:00:42,100 --> 00:00:44,100
♪But I heard the wind♪

10
00:00:44,220 --> 00:00:45,900
♪From the sea and the sky♪

11
00:00:46,180 --> 00:00:47,660
♪It said don't bend♪

12
00:00:47,780 --> 00:00:49,820
♪Bow your head, and your chains begin♪

13
00:00:49,940 --> 00:00:51,380
♪You are the wave♪

14
00:00:51,500 --> 00:00:53,300
♪And the wind that won't behave♪

15
00:00:53,380 --> 00:00:56,340
♪How could you be chained?♪

16
00:00:56,740 --> 00:00:58,740
♪Untamed, uncaged, unclaimed♪

17
00:00:58,780 --> 00:01:00,540
♪You're the blade in my gaze♪

18
00:01:00,620 --> 00:01:02,420
♪This world will leave you no space♪

19
00:01:02,500 --> 00:01:04,220
♪Then pierce it with your blaze♪

20
00:01:04,220 --> 00:01:06,100
♪My silent grind♪

21
00:01:06,100 --> 00:01:08,060
♪My aching pain♪

22
00:01:08,060 --> 00:01:10,300
♪Will one day turn...♪

23
00:01:11,860 --> 00:01:14,620
♪I am who I am♪

24
00:01:14,620 --> 00:01:18,140
♪My greatest ambition♪

25
00:01:18,220 --> 00:01:21,300
♪If the world can't contain me♪

26
00:01:21,380 --> 00:01:24,940
♪Then I'll break through it♪

27
00:01:25,420 --> 00:01:26,940
♪Become who I am♪

28
00:01:26,940 --> 00:01:28,260
[Wild Ambition Bloom]

29
00:01:28,260 --> 00:01:29,980
[Adapted from Stone and Water's novel,
The Uncaged Flame]

30
00:01:29,980 --> 00:01:32,980
[Episode 6]

31
00:01:33,040 --> 00:01:33,770
Shaohua.

32
00:01:34,950 --> 00:01:36,820
How can I ever repay you?

33
00:01:39,510 --> 00:01:41,050
Live happily,

34
00:01:41,120 --> 00:01:42,330
beautifully,

35
00:01:42,950 --> 00:01:44,130
and with dignity.

36
00:01:46,680 --> 00:01:48,260
Okay, I will.

37
00:01:50,590 --> 00:01:51,820
What are your plans after this?

38
00:01:54,310 --> 00:01:55,290
I want to go to Shanghai.

39
00:01:56,230 --> 00:01:56,980
Shanghai?

40
00:02:00,000 --> 00:02:01,660
Why do you want to go there?

41
00:02:02,480 --> 00:02:04,380
Some of my customers
from Shanghai told me

42
00:02:04,680 --> 00:02:06,620
Shanghai is more prosperous
than Peking,

43
00:02:07,120 --> 00:02:08,170
and there are more opportunities there.

44
00:02:08,400 --> 00:02:09,290
I want to give it a try.

45
00:02:11,000 --> 00:02:11,660
Oh, right.

46
00:02:12,360 --> 00:02:13,610
Before you leave,

47
00:02:13,960 --> 00:02:16,260
there's one more thing
you need to settle.

48
00:02:29,360 --> 00:02:31,290
Mrs. Chen Junior, I apologize.

49
00:02:31,520 --> 00:02:32,940
Though it's been delayed for a few days,

50
00:02:33,030 --> 00:02:34,850
I've completed the task

51
00:02:34,870 --> 00:02:35,980
you entrusted me with.

52
00:02:36,030 --> 00:02:37,220
Thank you, Mr. Zhao.

53
00:02:38,590 --> 00:02:39,410
You know what?

54
00:02:40,150 --> 00:02:42,820
I've been in this business
for so many years,

55
00:02:43,800 --> 00:02:45,060
but I've never seen

56
00:02:45,520 --> 00:02:46,610
such a stubborn scoundrel.

57
00:02:46,960 --> 00:02:47,660
Really?

58
00:02:48,910 --> 00:02:49,540
Alright then.

59
00:02:50,080 --> 00:02:52,010
Since he's here,

60
00:02:52,030 --> 00:02:53,130
how to deal with him

61
00:02:53,520 --> 00:02:54,540
is your call.

62
00:02:54,910 --> 00:02:55,780
See you later.

63
00:02:55,800 --> 00:02:56,450
See you.

64
00:03:04,710 --> 00:03:05,380
I don't know.

65
00:03:06,150 --> 00:03:07,540
I don't know any top-notch Renshen.

66
00:03:08,360 --> 00:03:09,130
I have never seen it.

67
00:03:09,680 --> 00:03:10,850
You've got the wrong person.

68
00:03:11,430 --> 00:03:12,890
I really don't know
any top-notch Renshen.

69
00:03:13,360 --> 00:03:14,540
Of course you don't.

70
00:03:17,470 --> 00:03:18,260
Who are you?

71
00:03:18,560 --> 00:03:19,730
That doesn't matter.

72
00:03:20,680 --> 00:03:21,850
Look who it is.

73
00:03:31,710 --> 00:03:32,610
Wu.

74
00:03:33,910 --> 00:03:35,010
Do you still recognize me?

75
00:03:36,710 --> 00:03:37,540
Erniu.

76
00:03:42,030 --> 00:03:42,820
Erniu.

77
00:03:46,030 --> 00:03:47,130
So you still remember me.

78
00:03:47,400 --> 00:03:48,100
Erniu.

79
00:03:48,910 --> 00:03:49,540
Erniu.

80
00:03:50,800 --> 00:03:52,410
I can't believe I get to see you again.

81
00:03:53,280 --> 00:03:54,730
I can go in peace now.

82
00:03:55,310 --> 00:03:57,130
Surprised to see me, right?

83
00:03:58,710 --> 00:03:59,410
Erniu.

84
00:04:01,080 --> 00:04:01,820
Erniu.

85
00:04:03,470 --> 00:04:04,410
I failed you.

86
00:04:05,310 --> 00:04:06,340
I'm sorry, I let you down.

87
00:04:07,280 --> 00:04:08,570
I'm not even human.

88
00:04:09,800 --> 00:04:11,660
Now you know you're not human?

89
00:04:12,280 --> 00:04:13,220
After you left,

90
00:04:13,800 --> 00:04:16,140
I've been living in pain and regret.

91
00:04:17,040 --> 00:04:19,660
I wished I could kill myself.

92
00:04:20,430 --> 00:04:22,340
You were suffering in Linfang Pavilion,

93
00:04:23,750 --> 00:04:24,660
while I was outside,

94
00:04:25,800 --> 00:04:28,050
tormented!

95
00:04:28,800 --> 00:04:30,460
But what's the use

96
00:04:31,360 --> 00:04:32,660
of saying all this now?

97
00:04:32,800 --> 00:04:34,340
I know it's useless.

98
00:04:36,630 --> 00:04:38,100
I only ask one thing of you.

99
00:04:38,510 --> 00:04:39,810
Let me

100
00:04:40,430 --> 00:04:43,170
make it up to you.

101
00:04:44,830 --> 00:04:46,100
So, how are you planning to do that?

102
00:04:46,870 --> 00:04:48,100
Before my time runs out,

103
00:04:48,560 --> 00:04:49,980
let me stay with you

104
00:04:51,310 --> 00:04:52,050
and take care of you.

105
00:04:52,750 --> 00:04:53,850
I'll do nothing else

106
00:04:54,040 --> 00:04:55,170
but treat you right,

107
00:04:56,360 --> 00:04:57,100
just like I used to.

108
00:05:00,820 --> 00:05:01,730
Like you used to?

109
00:05:02,390 --> 00:05:04,140
Yes.

110
00:05:04,830 --> 00:05:05,490
Erniu,

111
00:05:06,060 --> 00:05:07,020
do you still remember?

112
00:05:08,070 --> 00:05:08,700
Back then,

113
00:05:09,430 --> 00:05:12,220
whenever I had time, I'd come find you.

114
00:05:13,060 --> 00:05:14,140
Whatever you wanted to eat,

115
00:05:14,700 --> 00:05:16,610
I'd get it for you.

116
00:05:17,390 --> 00:05:19,370
Even if I was down
to my last bit of money,

117
00:05:19,830 --> 00:05:21,370
I'd spend it all on you.

118
00:05:21,900 --> 00:05:24,100
You were good to me, indeed.

119
00:05:24,630 --> 00:05:25,980
And I will be, too.

120
00:05:26,460 --> 00:05:27,370
Even better than before.

121
00:05:27,830 --> 00:05:28,980
After all these years,

122
00:05:29,630 --> 00:05:30,540
I've come to realize

123
00:05:31,140 --> 00:05:32,340
that being poor,

124
00:05:32,750 --> 00:05:34,780
being lied to, even being beaten,

125
00:05:35,830 --> 00:05:38,100
none of them hurt as much as losing you.

126
00:05:38,630 --> 00:05:41,490
Now I finally see
how much you mean to me.

127
00:05:43,390 --> 00:05:44,170
Got it.

128
00:05:45,020 --> 00:05:46,580
I know, Erniu.

129
00:05:46,750 --> 00:05:47,850
You've always been

130
00:05:48,380 --> 00:05:50,460
the closest one to me
who's treated me best.

131
00:05:50,950 --> 00:05:53,100
I can't bear to lose you.

132
00:05:54,630 --> 00:05:56,370
Is that truly how you feel?

133
00:05:56,830 --> 00:05:57,810
I mean every word.

134
00:06:01,460 --> 00:06:02,980
Stick out your tongue.

135
00:06:04,020 --> 00:06:05,410
Let me have a good look at it.

136
00:06:05,900 --> 00:06:07,460
Who would've thought

137
00:06:08,510 --> 00:06:10,610
you'd say something so beautiful?

138
00:06:11,220 --> 00:06:12,220
Stick it out.

139
00:06:28,620 --> 00:06:30,220
[Chen's Apothecary]

140
00:06:34,510 --> 00:06:35,100
Do you remember this?

141
00:06:35,560 --> 00:06:36,290
A few days ago,

142
00:06:36,800 --> 00:06:38,050
I went to collect a debt
with Mrs. Chen Junior,

143
00:06:38,830 --> 00:06:40,020
We met her old friend

144
00:06:40,040 --> 00:06:41,490
at Linfang Pavilion.

145
00:06:42,950 --> 00:06:44,170
I heard you mention it before.

146
00:06:44,720 --> 00:06:46,290
I thought that was the end of it.

147
00:06:46,830 --> 00:06:47,780
But then, a couple of days ago,

148
00:06:48,390 --> 00:06:50,250
she actually spent
hundreds of silver dollars

149
00:06:50,390 --> 00:06:51,780
to redeem her friend.

150
00:06:52,240 --> 00:06:53,540
That's no small amount.

151
00:06:54,120 --> 00:06:54,780
That's why

152
00:06:55,240 --> 00:06:56,490
her character

153
00:06:56,720 --> 00:06:57,780
- is truly beyond words.
- Hey, you.

154
00:06:57,800 --> 00:06:58,850
Zhuang,

155
00:07:00,560 --> 00:07:01,460
what friend

156
00:07:01,480 --> 00:07:03,220
were you talking about?

157
00:07:04,800 --> 00:07:06,980
We were talking about...

158
00:07:07,560 --> 00:07:08,730
the play Zhuang saw yesterday.

159
00:07:09,240 --> 00:07:09,810
Yes.

160
00:07:09,830 --> 00:07:12,050
Madam, I caught a play last night.

161
00:07:13,160 --> 00:07:14,580
What hundreds of silver dollars?

162
00:07:16,120 --> 00:07:17,700
It was in the script.

163
00:07:20,430 --> 00:07:21,340
Went to see a play last night?

164
00:07:21,750 --> 00:07:23,170
Yes, a play.

165
00:07:30,120 --> 00:07:32,520
[Peking]

166
00:07:40,040 --> 00:07:40,700
Shaohua.

167
00:07:41,430 --> 00:07:41,780
Erniu.

168
00:07:41,800 --> 00:07:42,370
I'm here.

169
00:07:44,920 --> 00:07:46,020
Finally made it.

170
00:07:46,830 --> 00:07:47,930
You brought Xuan.

171
00:07:47,950 --> 00:07:49,900
Yes, that's why

172
00:07:49,920 --> 00:07:50,900
I'm late.

173
00:07:50,920 --> 00:07:52,220
I wanted her to meet you.

174
00:07:52,240 --> 00:07:53,460
But she's asleep.

175
00:07:53,480 --> 00:07:54,460
So adorable.

176
00:07:57,160 --> 00:07:57,900
Shaohua,

177
00:07:59,040 --> 00:07:59,930
I will never get

178
00:08:00,190 --> 00:08:01,850
to be a mother.

179
00:08:03,390 --> 00:08:04,050
Erniu,

180
00:08:04,800 --> 00:08:06,220
Xuan is your daughter.

181
00:08:08,270 --> 00:08:09,140
I'll take her

182
00:08:10,270 --> 00:08:12,980
to Shanghai to see you.

183
00:08:14,040 --> 00:08:14,730
Definitely.

184
00:08:18,390 --> 00:08:20,370
Right, take this.

185
00:08:21,360 --> 00:08:22,730
Then I'll accept it.

186
00:08:23,360 --> 00:08:25,050
This contains the Chen family's address.

187
00:08:25,070 --> 00:08:25,850
I'll always be there.

188
00:08:26,510 --> 00:08:27,540
As soon as you arrive in Shanghai,

189
00:08:27,800 --> 00:08:30,610
make sure to write to me.

190
00:08:30,630 --> 00:08:31,340
I know.

191
00:08:32,600 --> 00:08:33,300
Shaohua,

192
00:08:33,510 --> 00:08:34,700
this time,

193
00:08:35,030 --> 00:08:36,490
I will return with glory.

194
00:08:38,720 --> 00:08:39,420
Erniu,

195
00:08:42,200 --> 00:08:44,100
I only hope you stay safe and sound.

196
00:08:46,360 --> 00:08:47,130
Don't worry.

197
00:08:49,870 --> 00:08:50,650
I have to go.

198
00:08:53,360 --> 00:08:53,980
Go.

199
00:09:02,360 --> 00:09:03,180
Watch your step.

200
00:09:03,480 --> 00:09:04,220
Shaohua,

201
00:09:05,000 --> 00:09:06,180
look after yourself, okay?

202
00:09:06,480 --> 00:09:07,650
Don't worry about me.

203
00:09:08,200 --> 00:09:08,940
Go back.

204
00:09:09,120 --> 00:09:10,530
You must take good care of yourself.

205
00:09:30,670 --> 00:09:32,060
Stay safe and sound.

206
00:09:39,030 --> 00:09:40,300
Hundreds of silver dollars?

207
00:09:42,840 --> 00:09:44,220
Which assistant told you that?

208
00:09:45,390 --> 00:09:46,980
It was the thin, dark one.

209
00:09:48,960 --> 00:09:49,940
Shitou.

210
00:09:51,390 --> 00:09:52,820
He has always been prudent

211
00:09:53,080 --> 00:09:54,490
and rarely speaks carelessly.

212
00:09:55,320 --> 00:09:56,490
I'm sure

213
00:09:56,630 --> 00:09:57,730
Shaohua's been

214
00:09:57,910 --> 00:09:59,850
secretly sending money

215
00:10:00,030 --> 00:10:01,250
back to her family.

216
00:10:02,030 --> 00:10:03,530
I told you

217
00:10:03,630 --> 00:10:06,490
not to let our son marry someone
from a poor family.

218
00:10:07,000 --> 00:10:07,770
You wouldn't listen.

219
00:10:08,240 --> 00:10:10,460
Hundreds of silver dollars!

220
00:10:10,720 --> 00:10:12,060
If she keeps this up,

221
00:10:12,360 --> 00:10:13,460
we'll be wiped out

222
00:10:13,510 --> 00:10:16,300
before the year's over.

223
00:10:16,960 --> 00:10:18,610
Shut up!

224
00:10:20,120 --> 00:10:21,010
For heaven's sake!

225
00:10:25,390 --> 00:10:26,060
Shaohua.

226
00:10:26,600 --> 00:10:27,250
Song Ping.

227
00:10:27,270 --> 00:10:28,730
You're finally back.

228
00:10:28,750 --> 00:10:29,370
Something happened.

229
00:10:30,750 --> 00:10:31,460
What's wrong?

230
00:10:33,870 --> 00:10:34,580
Thanks.

231
00:10:36,910 --> 00:10:37,610
What's wrong?

232
00:10:37,960 --> 00:10:39,100
Father is beating Dashun.

233
00:10:40,580 --> 00:10:42,460
He stole 200 from the shop's accounts

234
00:10:42,460 --> 00:10:43,340
and was discovered.

235
00:10:49,020 --> 00:10:51,020
Dashun, you must tell the truth.

236
00:10:51,380 --> 00:10:52,980
Did your wife take that money?

237
00:10:53,020 --> 00:10:53,740
No.

238
00:10:54,780 --> 00:10:56,020
It has nothing to do with Shaohua.

239
00:10:57,220 --> 00:10:58,260
I embezzled it.

240
00:10:58,420 --> 00:11:00,420
What did you do with that money?

241
00:11:00,580 --> 00:11:01,300
I...

242
00:11:02,420 --> 00:11:05,740
I spent it... on drinking and gambling.

243
00:11:07,140 --> 00:11:07,660
I...

244
00:11:08,340 --> 00:11:09,340
Get the rod!

245
00:11:10,100 --> 00:11:10,820
Father.

246
00:11:11,620 --> 00:11:12,260
Shaohua,

247
00:11:12,500 --> 00:11:13,780
this has nothing to do with you.
Go back to our room.

248
00:11:13,780 --> 00:11:14,780
- Did you hear me?
- Don't be angry.

249
00:11:14,780 --> 00:11:15,340
Please calm down.

250
00:11:15,340 --> 00:11:15,940
Shaohua!

251
00:11:16,780 --> 00:11:19,180
Shaohua, be honest,

252
00:11:19,220 --> 00:11:20,780
what have you done?

253
00:11:21,380 --> 00:11:22,020
Father,

254
00:11:22,660 --> 00:11:25,300
the money was embezzled by Dashun,

255
00:11:26,100 --> 00:11:28,580
but he did it because of me.

256
00:11:29,500 --> 00:11:30,700
Shaohua, what are you doing?

257
00:11:32,220 --> 00:11:33,420
See?

258
00:11:33,500 --> 00:11:34,700
I told you!

259
00:11:34,700 --> 00:11:35,540
Alright.

260
00:11:36,100 --> 00:11:36,700
Speak.

261
00:11:37,980 --> 00:11:39,380
What did you do with that money?

262
00:11:40,100 --> 00:11:41,900
A childhood friend of mine

263
00:11:43,100 --> 00:11:44,300
was deceived by some bad people

264
00:11:46,180 --> 00:11:48,340
and ended up in Linfang Pavilion.

265
00:11:49,420 --> 00:11:50,740
I wanted to redeem her freedom,

266
00:11:51,540 --> 00:11:53,180
but I didn't have enough money.

267
00:11:53,580 --> 00:11:55,620
Dashun found out and wanted to help me,

268
00:11:55,780 --> 00:11:57,180
that's why he borrowed 200

269
00:11:57,900 --> 00:11:58,940
from our shop's accounts.

270
00:11:59,900 --> 00:12:01,940
What kind of place is Linfang Pavilion?

271
00:12:02,900 --> 00:12:05,820
You spent money
to bail out someone like that?

272
00:12:07,460 --> 00:12:09,460
Even Ershun wouldn't do such a thing.

273
00:12:10,500 --> 00:12:11,300
Absurd!

274
00:12:13,140 --> 00:12:14,460
Father, Mother,

275
00:12:14,940 --> 00:12:16,300
don't blame Dashun.

276
00:12:16,860 --> 00:12:18,220
This all started because of me.

277
00:12:18,380 --> 00:12:20,580
I'll face the consequences.

278
00:12:20,740 --> 00:12:22,780
Father, I was the one
who took the money.

279
00:12:22,780 --> 00:12:23,980
Shaohua had nothing to do with it.

280
00:12:24,140 --> 00:12:25,260
Let me take the punishment.

281
00:12:25,460 --> 00:12:27,660
Can you get the money back?

282
00:12:29,140 --> 00:12:30,140
Mother, don't worry.

283
00:12:30,540 --> 00:12:31,540
I'll pay it back

284
00:12:32,020 --> 00:12:33,740
before the year's over.

285
00:12:35,140 --> 00:12:36,660
What you eat, what you use,

286
00:12:36,660 --> 00:12:37,860
and the house you live in

287
00:12:38,020 --> 00:12:39,300
are all provided by us.

288
00:12:39,540 --> 00:12:40,500
How will you pay it back?

